First Task - Algorithm for Dot Product and Orthogonality Check:

Algorithm: dot_product(v1, v2)
Input: v1 and v2 (vectors of IR, having the same length)

Variables:
ps = 0

For i = 0 to length of v1 - 1:
ps = ps + v1[i] * v2[i]

Output: ps

Algorithm: check_orthogonality(n, v1_list, v2_list)
Input: n (number of vector pairs), v1_list, and v2_list (arrays containing n pairs of vectors)

For i = 0 to n - 1:
dot_prod = dot_product(v1_list[i], v2_list[i])
If dot_prod = 0:
Print "Vectors v1 and v2 are orthogonal."
Else:
Print "Vectors v1 and v2 are not orthogonal."